          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/tfmt-000R.xml" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="forest://forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">tree</fr:link> in <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/index.xml" title="Forester" addr="forest://forester/index" type="local">Forester</fr:link> is a single file written in a markup language designed specifically for scientific writing <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-007L.xml" title="Bottom-up hierarchy via transclusion" addr="forest://forester/jms-007L" type="local">with bottom-up hierarchy via transclusion</fr:link>. A <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/tfmt-000R.xml" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="forest://forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">tree</fr:link> has two components: the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-007P.xml" title="Forester markup: frontmatter" addr="forest://forester/jms-007P" type="local">frontmatter</fr:link> and the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-007O.xml" title="Forester markup: mainmatter" addr="forest://forester/jms-007O" type="local">mainmatter</fr:link>.</html:p>
